A bash template contains the basic components that we usually write on the script. <br>
It may contains a Help facility, a licensing statement, a number of simple functions and some logic. <br>
<br>
<br>
#!/bin/bash <br>
############################################################## <br>
#                      scriptTemplate                        # <br>
#                                                            # <br>
# Use this template as the beginning of a new program. Place # <br>
# a short description of the script here.                    # <br>
#                                                            # <br>
# Change History                                             # <br>
# 01/05/2020   Yongki    This is a template for creating new # <br>
#                        Bash shell scripts.                 # <br>
#                        Add new history entries as needed   # <br>
#                                                            # <br>
#                                                            # <br> 
#                                                            # <br>
############################################################## <br>
